column26: Pivotal Trial to Evaluate the Safety and Efficacy of the Diamondback 360 Orbital Atherectomy System in Treating De Novo, Severely Calcified Coronary Lesions ORBIT II. This is a prospective, single-arm, multi-center study to evaluate the safety and performance of the OAS in treating de novo, severely calcified coronary lesions in adult subjects.

Complete Lesion Assessment With ffR and IVUS TechnologY CLARITY I. CLARITY I is a pilot study to identify the clinically appropriate endpoints of a larger, statistically powered pivotal trial for treatment of patients with Critical Limb Ischemia CLI.

Complete Lesion Assessment With ffR and IVUS TechnologY CLARITY I. CLARITY I is a pilot study to identify the clinically appropriate endpoints of a larger, statistically powered pivotal trial for treatment of patients with Critical Limb Ischemia CLI.

Pivotal Trial to Evaluate the Safety and Efficacy of the Diamondback 360 Orbital Atherectomy System in Treating De Novo, Severely Calcified Coronary Lesions ORBIT II. This is a prospective, single-arm, multi-center study to evaluate the safety and performance of the OAS in treating de novo, severely calcified coronary lesions in adult subjects.

LIBERTY 360 Prospective, Observational, Multi-Center Clinical Study to Evaluate Acute and Long Term Clinical and Economic Outcomes of Endovascular Device Intervention in Patients With Distal Outflow Peripheral Arterial Disease PAD.  The purpose of this study is to evaluate acute and long term clinical and economic outcomes of endovascular procedures to treat Peripheral Arterial Disease PAD.
